lbtt
------------------------------------------
lbtt is a tool for testing programs that translate formulas expressed in
propositional linear temporal logic (LTL) into B端chi automata. The goal of the
tool is to assist in the correct implementation of LTL-to-B端chi translation
algorithms by providing an automated testing environment for LTL-to-B端chi
translators. Additionally, the testing environment can be used for very basic
profiling of different LTL-to-B端chi translators to evaluate their performance.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.5-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libreadline8-8.3-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  bison-3.8.2-1
  cygport-0.37.4-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libreadline-devel-8.3-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.tcs.hut.fi/Software/lbtt/

Canonical download:
  http://www.tcs.hut.fi/Software/lbtt/releases/1.2/lbtt-1.2.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack lbtt-1.2.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./lbtt-1.2.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/lbtt-1.2.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/lbtt-1.2.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(lbtt)
  /usr/bin/lbtt-translate.exe
  /usr/bin/lbtt.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/lbtt.README
  /usr/share/doc/lbtt/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/lbtt/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/lbtt/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/lbtt/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/lbtt/README
  /usr/share/info/lbtt.info.gz

